body.text: The board is a 2D canvas with a physics engine. Gravity makes sprites fall and boundary makes them bounce.
Display the board. The game loop will start after leaving main.

JnEqsHAQ7isQH2J01rI3ytI6.text: Checks if user press LEFT, RIGHT or SHOOT buttons and responds accordingly

jCa9UoldbjXoNti9Q44vwynn.text: Check if the user base hits the left hand side of the screen & stop it from going out

sagB3vIzTvHQEr0TJ5EYaqBI.text: Check if the user base hits the right hand side of the screen and stop it from going out

PMvnDY4Bc14K999JRstkqomf.text: Check if laser hits user controlled base and subtract a life if it does and reset the laser

FCn9S224bOoC7r8Pggzyj5OV.text: If rocket leaves the screen reset it

KOTssomfgkkJSubmvoPVjYhA.text: Check if alien laser hits the shields and remove the shield if it does

xRRq8P0HHAoQOcGDgWjAc1Z2.text: Hide shield off screen and then remove it from the sprite set

Cq26iRPPrsUqVa06ua02P2VL.text: If alien is above user base and laser is NOT currently being fired, then fire it

FBnoIOaePy896Nm1OeWfesV9.text: Check if Alien is hit by the rocket from the user base

ReYYOtkJ0trnuMV9ZHhwHZD8.text: If all the aliens have been destroyed spawn a new wave of them

TqJCqMlA0Om5919ufdiY4yNf.text: This creates rows and columns of alien invaders

cbmb09vCaemz2ExJqvQMj7t0.text: This creates rows and columns of shields using rectangles

V9WkMybYkMHVaU4xqx1y6Ype.text: This function moves the aliens left and right and then down when they hit either side.

app.comment:
#pilvu2

I found a way to do a touch and hold event, but had to code it a different way as the touch sprite event doesn't allow for this at present. So you can now hold down the left and right buttons to move. I also added shields to make it a little easier on the first wave.
